%Now, we are going to use a .yaml file to configure our pyradionomics; in Layman's terms, we are going to tell it exactly what we want to extract from the images)
%Back at the terminal, in your command line, type in source ./final.yaml (you can change this, but you will have to adjust this in your Step 1 script accordingly when you call it
%Copy and paste the following, note that all of the first-order statistics aren't necessary for this particular case, but are included in this master script for thoroughness

%Start
# PyRadiomics configuration file

setting:
  binWidth: 25
  resampledPixelSpacing: [1, 1, 1]
  interpolator: 'sitkBSpline'
  correctMask: True

imageType:
  Original: {}

featureClass:                
  firstorder: []

%End

Press Ctrl O to save, click enter, press Ctrl X and enter to exit back to command line

#Details
#We are obtaining all first-order statistics with this, if you want only the mean to reduce computational need, then you can adjust accordingly
